Chloe pulled her car to a stop in back of Lex’s Jaguar and arched an eyebrow at him.  <br>
<br>
“Interesting choice of music, Luthor,” she said with a teasing smile.  “I was expecting something more along the lines of Audioslave or Biohazard from you.”  He smirked at her.<br>
<br>
“If we were in my car, then maybe,” he said.  “Speaking of which ---” Lex motioned to his car with his head.  <br>
<br>
“I’ve taken up enough of your time today,” she filled in for him.  He gave her a bemused look and tilted his head slightly as he opened the door.<br>
<br>
“Actually, I was going to ask if you wanted that test drive now; but if you’ve changed your mind ---” he trailed off when he saw Chloe’s face light up.  <br>
<br>
“Really?!”<br>
<br>
“Well ---”<br>
<br>
She jumped out of the car and ran over to him the second she saw the smirk on his lips.  She rose to her tiptoes and threw her arms around him in an emotional hug.  Lex was so surprised by the action that he didn’t have time to embrace her before she pulled away.  She stayed on her tiptoes and kissed his cheek.<br>
<br>
“Thank you, thank you, thank you, Lex.  You won’t regret this,” Chloe said giddily.  Lex chuckled lightly and lowered his mouth to hers for a soft kiss.<br>
<br>
“I know.”<br>
